<recipe>
    <name>Mojo Pork</name>
    <indexCharacter>M</indexCharacter>
    <notes></notes>
    <servings>0</servings>
    <instructions>1. Puree first 9 ingredients a in a blender. Add oil gradually as machine continues to mix. Season with salt and pepper.

2. Transfer ½ cup of the Mojo marinade into a small dish; cover and refrigerate. This can be reheated and used as a dipping sauce later.

3. Place the pork tenderloins in a plastic sealable bag. Pour remaining mojo marinade over the pork. Seal bag and refrigerate overnight

4. Preheat grill to 350ºF

5. Remove pork from marinade. Remove excess marinade from the meat and season meat with salt and pepper. Oil grill and barbecue pork for 15-18 minutes, turning every 4 minutes to create, even golden browning

6. Remove pork, tent with aluminium foil and leave to rest for 10 minutes before serving.

7. Warm reserved Mojo and use as a dipping sauce</instructions>
